# Simulated ARGs

For simulated ARGs, we ran with 10 and 100 trees, and with/without the exponential growth simplification
(see "USE_EXP" in the python script - using this simplification removes one parameter, and helps both
 gLike and mrpast in analyzing this model).

Using 10 trees and the exponential growth simplification produced the best results.
Our reported results are from:
```
USE_EXP=1 TREES10=1 python glike.1t12.py 1t12_50.simdata/1t12_50_sim__0-0.trees 1t12_50.simdata/1t12_50_sim__0-0.trees.popmap.json
```

We ran this 50 times, once for each of the same simulated replicates that we used with mrpast.

# tsinfer ARGs

We used the same configuration as with the simulated ARGs (it also produced the best results on inferred ARGs).

```
USE_EXP=1 TREES10=1 python glike.1t12.py 0_tsinfer/1t121t12___0-0.trees.vcz.tsdate.trees 0_simdata_1t12/1t12___0-0.trees.popmap.json
```
